result.execSummary:
The defendant Autumn R Ostrowski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide [Modifiers: Solicitation of], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).
  • 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide [Modifiers: Solicitation of], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Autumn R Ostrowski in court with attorney Harry R Hertel.  Andrea A Nodolf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State calls Lt. Kevin Julien, oath given.  Direct by the State.  Objection by Defense. Sustained.  Objection, overruled.  Objection, sustained.  Cross by Atty Hartel.  Objection by the State, sustained.  Atty Hartel asks that the testimony be stricken and the court reporter read back the question, Court will strike the ans, but Atty Hartel reasks the question.  Objection by the state, sustained.  Objection, sustained.  Objection, sustained.  Atty Hartel requests to see documents that the witness reviewed this morning before testifying.  State objects.  Atty Hartel states statue to the court that this is allowed.  Court will grant reviewing of this material.  Atty Hartel requests adjourning today's prelim to another date to allowing time to review the material.  State can supply material to Atty Hartel within half an hour.  Court will reconven after viewing of the material.  9:53 AM court is back in session.  Witness still under oath, testimony continues.  Objection by the State, sustained.  Witness dismissed.  Argument by Atty Hartel.  Court will bind over for trial, court finds probable cause.  State files information this day in court.  Atty/Def will waive time limits, wishes to revisit the issue of bond.  Set for arraignment 6-10-14 @ 8:30AM.  On the issue of bond, Defense requests a $10,000.00 cash bond, house arrest and electronic monitoring at the expense of the Ostrowski family.  Also asking for supervised visitations with the children shared with Mackenzie Anderson.  State objects to reduction of the bond, also objects to the visitation of the children with M. A. has no objection to supervised visitation with the child not shared with M.A.  The court is satisfied the cash bond in the present form is adeqate, will not modify at this time.  Supervised visitation with the one child is approved by the court.  They will be supervised by the DHHS, no discussion of this case with the children.  Per the Jail policy,  these visits will need to be completed in the Jail.
